				<exercise>
			<p>Shown above is a charge diagram for a disc.  Indicate the location with the greatest charge density.</p>
			</exercise>
			<exercise>
			<p>Make a charge diagram for each of the following charge densities.  What is the purpose of the various constants in these expressions?
			<ul>
			<li><m>\lambda(x) = \lambda_1 x / L</m> between <m>x=-L</m> and <m>x=+L</m></li>
			<li><m>\lambda{y} = \frac{q_2}{y}</m> between <m>y=0</m> and <m>y=\inf</m></li>
			<li><m>\sigma{s,\theta} = \sigma_3 \frac{s^2}{R^2}</m> between <m>s=0</m> and <m>s=R</m>, where <m>s</m> points radially outward from the origin</li>
			</ul></p>
			</exercise>
